{
  "id": 5076349064708096,
  "name": "Deprecate and Remove: Shared Storage API",
  "summary": "The Shared Storage API is a privacy-preserving web API to enable storage that is not partitioned by first-party site.\n\nFollowing Chrome's announcement that the current approach to third-party cookies will be maintained, we are now planning to deprecate and remove the Shared Storage API (along with certain other Privacy Sandbox APIs, as outlined on the Privacy Sandbox feature status page).\n\n[0]: https://privacysandbox.com/news/privacy-sandbox-next-steps/",
